{"id":581025036,"lang":"java","time":"3 months, 3 weeks","timestamp":1635868469,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"4 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/581025036/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Two Sum IV - Input is a BST","memory":"41.3 MB","code":"/**\n * Definition for a binary tree node.\n * public class TreeNode {\n *     int val;\n *     TreeNode left;\n *     TreeNode right;\n *     TreeNode() {}\n *     TreeNode(int val) { this.val = val; }\n *     TreeNode(int val, TreeNode left, TreeNode right) {\n *         this.val = val;\n *         this.left = left;\n *         this.right = right;\n *     }\n * }\n */\nclass Solution {\n    Set<Integer> set = new HashSet<>();\n    public boolean findTarget(TreeNode root, int k) {\n        return inorder(root, k);\n    }\n    \n    private boolean inorder(TreeNode root, int k) {\n        boolean left = false, right = false, val = false;\n        if (root != null) {\n            left = inorder(root.left, k);\n            if (set.contains(k - root.val)) {\n                val = true;\n            } else\n                set.add(root.val);\n            right = inorder(root.right, k);\n        }\n        return left || right || val;\n    }\n}","compare_result":"","title_slug":"two-sum-iv-input-is-a-bst"}
